  "prompt": "Has a movie ever been shot in space?",
  "response": "Yes, a feature film has indeed been shot in space. The movie **\"The Challenge\"** (also known as **\"\u0412\u044b\u0437\u043e\u0432\"** in Russian), directed by Klim Shipenko, is the first feature film to include scenes shot in space. The project was a collaboration between the Russian space agency Roscosmos, the Russian television network Channel One, and the studio Yellow, Black and White.\n\nThe film stars Russian actress **Yulia Peresild**, who traveled to the International Space Station (ISS) in October 2021 alongside director Klim Shipenko and cosmonaut Anton Shkaplerov. The crew spent about 12 days aboard the ISS filming scenes for the movie. The storyline revolves around a surgeon (played by Peresild) who is sent to space to perform an operation on a cosmonaut.\n\nWhile space has been depicted in many films using special effects and soundstage recreations, \"The Challenge\" is the first to involve actual filming in orbit, marking a significant milestone in cinematic history.",
